                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320216-195-victim1623 t18320216-195-viclabel1099"></join>. I lost several bottles from my premises, and on the 19th of January I was watching with the constable, from about five o'clock in the evening till about nine - I then heard something, but as somebody came in with some horses at the time, I could not hear any thing more - I waited till they were gone, and then I heard some bottles move; I ran up, and found the prisoner with the bottles - they had been in a shed in my garden; he had only moved them about two yards from where he took them.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320216-195-person1625">
                  RICHARD 
                  MILLS
               <interp inst="t18320216-195-person1625" type="surname" value="MILLS"></interp>
